[67.409387, "o", "Done! The ODE solver is implemented at `/app/ode_solve.py`. \r\n\r\n**Key features:**\r\n- Uses RK4 (4th-order Runge-Kutta) for integration\r\n- Step size: h_max/2 = (t1-t0)/400 to satisfy the multi-stage safe bound\r\n- Lands exactly at each eval_t with final substep clamped\r\n- Evaluates `rhs` at each landing time (no interpolation)\r\n- Outputs `/app/output/solution.csv` with `t,y` format\r\n- Pure NumPy implementation (no black-box ODE libraries)\r\n\r\nThe solver will be tested against the harness-provided `ode_problem.py` which defines `t0`, `t1`, `y0`, `eval_ts`, and `rhs(t,y)`.\r\n"]
